item.title: These forums went back to the ice age
item.dc:creator: @Palidino76 Palidino76
item.description:
@Palidino76 wrote:

Just say it in English next time? What I think he means is MoparScape used to be filled with people posting and talking. But now, it seems it has died down tremendously, like when someone makes a forum theres not much posting going on because not many people know about it yet.

And I do agree, after the rules of the TUT section changed saying you could only post stuff that “taught” you something, the number of people posting there imdeiatly dropped because they couldn’t post c+p tuts (copy and paste).

And then came the advertisement section, or by that I mean they removed the advertisment section, which angered more than it pleased (although the same with the tut section), so people went on sorta like a rampage making their own forums and advertising them here, and people began to leave, one by one.

So basicly its dropped back down to be like a “new” forum even though its not, but the diffrence with that is it wont increase because people do not like these rules
